All of us here at Sherry’s were excited when we first tasted this 1938 Bourbon. It was superb, rich in flavor, yet remarkably delicate. There were only 280 cases in all Kentucky ~ we bought them all. Made at a small country distillery back in 1938, it was kept in oak barrel for 8 years until it achieved full maturation — then it was bottled-in-bond at 100 proof in 1946.
